summary: Star Wars: The Clone Wars Moments | 4x10 Carnage of Krell Rex ventures across the enemy lines, investigating the corpse of one...
caption:
Star Wars: The Clone Wars Moments | 4x10 Carnage of Krell

Rex ventures across the enemy lines, investigating the corpse of one of the supposedly “disguised” Umbarans; but to his horror, the soldier turns out to be a clone trooper from the 212th Attack Battalion. Realizing they have been deceived, Rex breaks into a run across the battlefield, frantically ordering his men to remove their helmets and reveal their true identity to their misled comrades.

title: A Close Read of Star Wars Rebels “Twin Suns” – Part 10 – Suns and Moons
excerpt: All Close Read Entries While most conversations in the fan community are focused on the last few minutes of the episode, my favorite parts involved Ezra and his journey. Most believe he was being a…
description:
It may be Part 10, but it also stands on its own. All other entries are here.

“Removing Obi-Wan and Maul from the context of Ezra’s story means you lose the connective tissue between their poignant final moments and the transformative power of empathy and what it meant for both Maul and Obi-Wan’s fates.”

Also: how Luke grew beyond Obi-Wan Kenobi.

blog.name: angryducktimemachine
blog.title: 30 nervous rats in a mandalorian armor

summary: Finally got my ass down to work over my clones and get some shit down so here we go. The updated version of “Sarlacc Squad”.-...
caption:
Finally got my ass down to work over my clones and get some shit down so here we go. The updated version of “Sarlacc Squad”.-

All expect Kix belong to me, Kix is @fleur-de-lill ‘s sweetheart.

More to them under the cut!

RC-2203 aka No-one:

No-one is a big sweetheart and cares a lot about his brothers and other people close to him. He was the Leader of his old Squad while still training on Kamino.

In one of the real-life simulations things went terrible wrong and three of his brothers died due to a wrong order by him. This event hit him very bad and left him unable to speak in the future. The fact that he is mute is also where his name eventually come from.

The Kamionans label him as ‘defect’ after that, actually planning to get rid of him which is mostly prevented thanks to the help of his brother left:

RC-1602 aka Gun:

Gun and No-one have been in the same squad since they were kids and they share a very deep emotional bound.

In difference from No-one Gun tends to be very reckless and loud, in action as well as in speech. He’s very loyal but troubles with things like personal space and showing affection. 

After the simulation that costed three of his brothers deaths he works as hard as possible to at least save No-one. He taught both of them sign language and you can often see him talking in it as well instead of speaking Basic.

Alpha 42 aka Same:

Same is the one who brought Sarlacc-Squad together, he convinced the Kamionans to let No-one join a new squad, in exchange he would work in a team as well, an action he refused to do before. 

Same comes off as grumpy and bitter but would die for his squad members at any given time. He absolutely hates the republic and how they treat the clones but refuses to let his brothers behind so stays inside of the GAR.

RC-2409 aka Kix:

[will be added as soon as fleur-de-lill wrote something]

No-one is a big sweetheart and cares a lot about his brothers and other people close to him. He was the Leader of his old Squad while still training on Kamino.

In one of the real-life simulations things went terrible wrong and three of his brothers died due to a wrong order by him. This event hit him very bad and left him unable to speak in the future. The fact that he is mute is also where his name eventually come from.

The Kamionans label him as ‘defect’ after that, actually planning to get rid of him which is mostly prevented thanks to the help of his brother left:

RC-1602 aka Gun:

Gun and No-one have been in the same squad since they were kids and they share a very deep emotional bound.

In difference from No-one Gun tends to be very reckless and loud, in action as well as in speech. He’s very loyal but troubles with things like personal space and showing affection. 

After the simulation that costed three of his brothers deaths he works as hard as possible to at least save No-one. He taught both of them sign language and you can often see him talking in it as well instead of speaking Basic.

Alpha 42 aka Same:

Same is the one who brought Sarlacc-Squad together, he convinced the Kamionans to let No-one join a new squad, in exchange he would work in a team as well, an action he refused to do before. 

Same comes off as grumpy and bitter but would die for his squad members at any given time. He absolutely hates the republic and how they treat the clones but refuses to let his brothers behind so stays inside of the GAR.

summary: “What are you doing here?” Character/Pairing: Lana Beniko x Reader (gender neutral) Fandom: Star Wars (The Old Republic) Words:...
body:
“What are you doing here?”

Character/Pairing: Lana Beniko x Reader (gender neutral)

Fandom: Star Wars (The Old Republic)

Words: 555

First Shortfic for NaNoWriMo 2018 ;) Requests are open, as always!

—–

As commander of the alliance on Odessen, you had lots of things to do. So had your second-in-command, the Sith Lady Lana Beniko. Most tasks you tried to finish together, because your friendship made you a good team. However, sometimes you were needed on opposite sides of the galaxy at the same time. Well, it was no problem because of her work! You trusted her with everything, even with your life. Nevertheless, it still bothered you to be separated from her, because of your emotions. In the time working with Lana, you grew very fond of her. Too fond for your likings even. But you never told her, you feared it would cause problems to the alliance. So you kept your mouth shut. After coming back from some riots on Tatooine, you landed on Odessen with nothing else in your mind than Lana and her skills regarding dealing with such problems. So, you didn’t think about your way back to the base and your feet took you to a small platform where you used to sit and think when only the peaceful sight of the planet could ease your mind. But this time, you were not the only person there. 

Normally, you’d felt this presence everywhere, but as lost in your thoughts as you were now, the sight of Lanas back caught you by surprise. She sat at the edge of the platform, her legs dangling off it. „Sit beside me, commander?“, she asked while staring onto the landscape which unfolded below her. You fulfilled her wish, took a deep breath and then you asked: „What are you doing here?“ Fixing your eyes on some kind of a bird in the distance, you heard her sight. „I often felt you being up here, commander.“, she started. „After all that happened, something has led me here. The view shows what fragile and non-permanent thing we try to defend. It’s simply beautiful and soothing to look at.“ You chuckled. „How poetic.“Then you two fell silent. Lana was right, all your existences were temporary. Something told you ‘now or never’, so after a few moments you whispered: „Well, its not as beautiful as you are.“ You didn’t need to look, you felt how she turned her head to face you. „What?“, she finally exclaimed.

You still stared into the distance, but no power, no rang, nothing could safe you from the blush growing on your face after hearing her amused tone. „My dear Lana, we faced a lot of dangers together and it’s not even nearly over. I can feel it.“ Now, you finally turned to her, grasped for her hand and cleared your throat. „I don’t care what you will think about me now, you deserve to know this.“ You sighted, searching for words. „You deserve to know that… that I love you. So much. If needed, I would burn a thousand planets for you. I would make you the galaxy as a gift, would even die for you.“ You saw her eyes grew wider. Squeezing her hand gently, you stammered: „I.. I would do everything for you.“ After a few seconds, she smiled at you and squeezed your hand back. „Better live for me, then. You know, despite you being my commander, I have to admit..“ She winked at you. „I love you, too.“
